records.addlTxt:
Defendant Cheyanne M Terlann in court with attorney Thomas R. Jones.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Deputy court clerk: LMS.  

The defendant has complied with the Deferred Prosecution Agreement.
On motion of the state, the court amended the charge to Possession of THC, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 961.41(3g)(e), a class U misdemeanor.   Court ordered entry of judgment of conviction to the amended charge.

Court orders defendant to pay a fine of $100.00 plus all cost, fees and surcharges, including DNA surcharge by 2/04/2015 or a civil judgment to be entered with tax intercept.  Bail on deposit to be applied if applicable.

*COURT DOES NOT SUSPEND DRIVING PRIVILEGES.
